  "prompt": "What is an example of a platform that leveraged another platform to gain users?",
  "response": "A notable example of a platform that leveraged another platform to gain users is **Instagram**. When Instagram first launched in 2010, it capitalized on the growing popularity of **Facebook** to rapidly acquire users. Here's how:\n\n1. **Integration with Facebook**: Instagram allowed users to easily share their photos directly to their Facebook profiles. This seamless integration exposed Instagram to Facebook's massive user base, driving organic growth.\n\n2. **Facebook's Network Effects**: By leveraging Facebook's social graph, Instagram gained visibility as users shared their Instagram posts on Facebook, encouraging their friends to join Instagram as well.\n\n3. **Acquisition by Facebook**: In 2012, Facebook acquired Instagram for $1 billion. This further solidified Instagram's ability to tap into Facebook's resources, infrastructure, and user base, accelerating its growth.\n\nBy strategically leveraging Facebook's ecosystem, Instagram quickly became one of the most popular social media platforms globally.",
